{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_Ok3eWXUNdxWuL1pOEhvMwZTJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Spec Interview Complete: TST-001\n\nThe spec has been updated with your answers:\n\n**Interview Answers Incorporated:**\n- **Q1 (B):** Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n- **Q2 (D):** No existing RBAC → build from scratch (overrides PRD assumption of existing JWT middleware)\n\n**Key Impact:**\nThe interview revealed a significant architectural change - the codebase has **no existing RBAC system**, so the implementation must build from scratch rather than extending existing middleware. The spec status is now `draft` pending plan review.\n\n**Spec Highlights:**\n| Section | Details |\n|---------|---------|\n| **API Coverage** | All POST/PUT/DELETE endpoints protected |\n| **Auth Model** | New RBAC middleware with JWT Bearer |\n| **Session Sync** | WebSocket push with Redux state updates |\n| **Audit Trail** | New `audit_log` table with role operations |\n| **Performance Target** | P95 latency ≤ 10ms at 1000 RPS |\n| **Rollout** | 4-phase: Backend → WebSocket → Frontend → E2E |\n\n**Open Questions (Non-blocker):**\n- Audit log retention beyond 90 days?\n- Should denied access attempts trigger security alerts?\n\n---\n\n**Next Step:** Derive tasks from the spec.\n\n```\n/feature-dev-aidd:tasks-new TST-001\n```"}],"model":"kimi-for-coding","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":26370,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available","prompt_tokens":26370,"cached_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9e2fa98-0945-4bc8-af60-92fe87412fab","uuid":"1bfa36c2-0e4a-4d9a-aa7b-d8aaf6fba440"}
